# English-only UI (managers)

Managers use the app in **English only**. No Dutch (or other languages) in user-visible copy.

## Scope

Applies to everything users see in the product:

- `src/app/**` pages (stocktake, ordering, prep list, admin, dashboard, kitchen, HACCP)
- `src/components/**` (callouts, forms, stepper, nav labels, buttons, placeholders, errors, confirmations)
- `aria-label`, `title`, `placeholder`, empty states, tooltips

## Not in scope (OK to stay Dutch)

- Code comments and JSDoc (prefer English when touching files)
- Database column names, API field names (`leverancier`, `datum`, …)
- Supplier legal names (“Van Gelder”, “Gédé”)
- Migration SQL, edge-function logs, emails **to suppliers** (unless user asks otherwise)
- Docs/scripts under `docs/` and `scripts/`

## Rules when editing

1. **Never** add Dutch UI strings, even “temporary” callouts or hints.
2. When copying patterns from old code, **translate** before committing.
3. Prefer plain international English: “Save”, “Loading…”, “No results”, not mixed NL/EN.
4. Use `en-GB` or `en-US` for `toLocaleString` in UI, not `nl-NL`.
5. Before finishing a UI task, grep `src/` for common Dutch words: `geen`, `niet`, `voor`, `Toon`, `Alleen`, `Opslaan`, `Laden`, `grondstof`, `leverancier`, `bijv.`, `Allergenen`, `Weergave`, `Nieuwe`, `Bestaande`, `ingevuld`, `Kip`, `marinade`.

## Examples

| Avoid | Use |
|-------|-----|
| Opslaan… | Saving… |
| Geen resultaten | No results |
| Alleen nog niet ingevuld | Only not counted yet |
| Vul … in | Enter … |
